      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The myth of meritocracy ignores the reality that starting lines are not equal, so praising hard work in a rigged system only masks the advantages of those born into wealth. When racial disparities in education, housing, and healthcare are ignored, the narrative that success is purely earned devalues the struggles of marginalized communities and justifies their continued exclusion. True equity requires acknowledging that structural barriers prevent genuine competition, making meritocracy a tool for the privileged rather than a path to fairness.",
